WEBVTT

00:00:04.437 --> 00:00:06.006
Takashi,
something awful has happened!

00:00:07.007 --> 00:00:08.074
Your brother, he...

00:00:15.115 --> 00:00:16.583
My friend told me...

00:00:17.751 --> 00:00:21.121
"Your brother's
been acting strange lately."

00:00:31.264 --> 00:00:34.801
I feel bad that you have to
go through this because of me.

00:00:45.478 --> 00:00:47.113
Kota! Kota!

00:00:48.014 --> 00:00:49.015
Don't look.

00:01:04.064 --> 00:01:06.032
Takashi, don't look!

00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.863
MR. MIKAMI'S CLASSROOM

00:01:38.798 --> 00:01:39.799
I...

00:01:44.204 --> 00:01:45.371
I'm okay now.

00:01:48.842 --> 00:01:50.310
So next...

00:01:51.211 --> 00:01:52.312
It's your turn.

00:02:15.502 --> 00:02:19.172
Light Fit Sanitary Napkins

00:02:30.650 --> 00:02:34.220
The Shocking Past of
the Bureaucrat-Turned-Teacher

00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:36.389
Involved in a Revolving Door Scandal

00:02:43.530 --> 00:02:46.399
Emotions become unstable
during menstruation

00:02:46.499 --> 00:02:48.601
so it's not unusual for
various things to happen.

00:02:49.235 --> 00:02:52.839
But you can buy
sanitary products at the school store

00:02:53.039 --> 00:02:55.441
and there are some stocked
in the restrooms too.

00:02:55.642 --> 00:02:58.111
Still, I was concerned because
she keeps coming here

00:02:58.211 --> 00:02:59.412
to ask for them lately.

00:02:59.979 --> 00:03:01.881
I'm heading to
the staff room for a moment.

00:03:01.981 --> 00:03:04.384
If anyone comes, could you
tell them I'll be right back?

00:03:35.114 --> 00:03:37.617
Could it be that
she couldn't afford them?

00:03:38.151 --> 00:03:40.320
I think that's a real possibility.

00:03:47.961 --> 00:03:50.897
You're frozen like a statue.
Are you okay?

00:03:51.197 --> 00:03:54.334
Sorry, I grew up with a brother...

00:03:54.534 --> 00:03:57.270
As a teacher, you can't avoid
dealing with these issues.

00:03:57.370 --> 00:04:01.641
But, are those things
really that expensive?

00:04:02.342 --> 00:04:04.310
At most, about 500 yen?

00:04:05.712 --> 00:04:08.147
Period poverty...

00:04:08.715 --> 00:04:10.416
That's what I was thinking.

00:04:12.252 --> 00:04:13.553
How is Shiiba's home situation?

00:04:14.520 --> 00:04:17.156
She lost her parents in
a car accident when she was little.

00:04:17.557 --> 00:04:19.726
She's currently being raised by
her paternal grandparents

00:04:19.826 --> 00:04:21.394
who run a traditional sweets shop.

00:04:21.761 --> 00:04:23.363
It wouldn't be surprising

00:04:23.429 --> 00:04:26.366
if her home environment
has changed drastically.

00:04:26.899 --> 00:04:27.934
That was careless of me.

00:04:28.234 --> 00:04:29.802
I'll arrange a meeting
with her right away.

00:04:31.871 --> 00:04:33.840
– Come in.
– Excuse me.

00:04:35.942 --> 00:04:39.312
– So this is where you were.
– Is something wrong?

00:04:43.016 --> 00:04:44.851
What is this about?

00:04:50.356 --> 00:04:52.225
– Isn't this bad?
– What?

00:04:54.827 --> 00:04:56.763
– Wait, what?
– What is this?

00:04:56.863 --> 00:04:58.464
– What is this?
– I don't know.

00:04:58.564 --> 00:04:59.565
The Shocking Past of
the Bureaucrat-Turned-Teacher

00:04:59.666 --> 00:05:00.700
His Brother Committed Suicide at
Keiryo Academy 22 Years Ago!

00:05:00.800 --> 00:05:01.834
Is this for real?

00:05:03.102 --> 00:05:04.137
I have no idea.

00:05:06.172 --> 00:05:07.573
Okami...

00:05:11.177 --> 00:05:13.012
That was over 20 years ago.

00:05:15.948 --> 00:05:17.717
But, for them to write about it...

00:05:17.850 --> 00:05:20.320
That kind of gossip article
isn't worth taking seriously.

00:05:23.489 --> 00:05:24.957
Can we start class?

00:05:40.073 --> 00:05:41.974
How can you stay so calm
when something like that

00:05:42.075 --> 00:05:43.209
is written about you?

00:05:43.576 --> 00:05:45.011
This doesn't concern you.

00:05:46.979 --> 00:05:48.414
I can't forgive this.

00:05:52.051 --> 00:05:53.052
Because...

00:05:54.520 --> 00:05:55.621
it does concern us.

00:05:59.192 --> 00:06:02.962
Okay, let's pick up from
where we left off yesterday.

00:06:04.030 --> 00:06:05.498
Page 181.

00:06:28.788 --> 00:06:31.090
Do you think it's true?

00:06:32.325 --> 00:06:34.093
What is it with bureaucrats?

00:06:34.961 --> 00:06:37.497
The spotlight only shines on us
at times like this.

00:06:38.598 --> 00:06:39.766
That's so true.

00:06:40.266 --> 00:06:42.168
You can really feel
the public's desire

00:06:42.235 --> 00:06:44.837
to see powerful people fall.

00:06:44.937 --> 00:06:48.074
It's a job that gets criticized
but never praised.

00:06:48.174 --> 00:06:49.609
That's what being a bureaucrat is.

00:06:50.009 --> 00:06:51.644
No wonder
fewer people want to do it.

